Lets try to recall what do we do in coin change , we go to every index and either pick or not pick the element.
Similarly , in this question , we go to every index and because we can pick atmost k elements so , we try all the possibilities of picking elements from 0 to min(piles[idx].size() , k ) and we have to take max of all the possibilities 
we tried and return . As simple as that. For the memoisation part , the two parameters that are changing are memoised to reduce the 
**Time complexity from O(K^n) to (O(k*n)**
