The maximum value will contain a certain number of elements from some stacks, therefore in this approach we visit each index and iterate through the different number of items we can take from that index, after which we move to the next index

Subproblems: S(index,k)=The maxium value that can be obtained if we have to take exactly k coins from piles[index:]

Relations: We can either:-
1. Not take any coins from pile[index]=ans1=S(index+1,k)
2. Take a certain coins, we will choose the number that maximises the value at the end=ans2=max{piles[index][j]+S(index+1,k-j-1) **for all** j **in** [0,min(k,piles[index].size)]}
The final answer: S(index,k)=max{ans1,ans2}

Base case: 
1. S(index,k)=0 if k==0
2. S(index,k)=INT_MIN if index>=n and k!=0

Original problem: S(0,K)

Time complexity: O(NK)xO(K)=O(NK^2)
