So it's very simple just fix the number of pens and calculate how many pencils you can buy with the leftover money. keep on doing that till the max no. of pens u can buy. 
and find the number of pen/ pencils that can be bought using division.
and to count the number of combinations.
Ex:- suppose you can buy 1 pen and 3 pencils.Thus for 1 pen you could have 0,1,2,3 pencils , so by observation you see the number of combinations = number of pencils+1;
and **solved!**
