(1)Initialise count to 0.(as return type is long long count variable is not int but long long.)

(2)Initialise another variable temp with total.

(3)if cost of both articles is less than total money we return 1

(4)Otherwise run a for loop from 0 to total/cost2 (here we are fixing count of pencils thus cost2 is used)

(5)decrease temp every time by i times cost of pencil(i times because i represents how many pencils have been bought already and temp will tell how much money is left to buy pens)

(6)Increase count by temp/cost1 + 1 times on every iteration of loop(divide by cost1 because these much pens can be bought +1 because total ways will be +1 of no. of pens bought)
Ex-when i=0 we buy 0 pencils and can buy 0,1,2 pens i.e., we can buy in 3 ways (0 pencil and 0 pens , 0 pencil and 1 pen, 0 pencil and 2 pens)

(7)At end of each iteration we reset temp to original total money

(8)At last return Count.   

