Fix the number of pencil and then find number of ways to take pens. For example if we take one pencil then the total cost will reduce by the cost of one pencil and now we need to find how many pens we can take with remaining money i.e. either 0, 1, 2....etc.


# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long waysToBuyPensPencils(int tot, int c1, int c2) {
        long long ans = 0;
        long long maxp = tot/c1;
        for(int i=0;i<=maxp;i++)
        {
            long long pen = (tot-(i*c1))/c2;
            ans+=(pen+1);
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

