### **Code:-**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumCardPickup(vector<int>& cards) {
        int n = cards.size(), mn = INT_MAX;
        unordered_map<int, int> mp;     // Store Card Value and its index

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            // If found in map
            if(mp.count(cards[i]))
            {
                // Find size of window from prev index to current index
                int prev = mp[cards[i]];
                mn = min(mn, i - prev + 1);
            }
            // If not found in map, insert it
            mp[cards[i]] = i;
        }

        return mn == INT_MAX ? -1 : mn;
    }
};
```

### Explanation:-

**m[cards[i]] -> Prev index of the number
i - m[cards[i]] + 1 is the window/subarray size starting from the prev index to current index.
For eg:
```[3, 4, 2, 3, 4, 7]```
When ```i = 3```, we encounter 3 again. In the map, we have stored ```index of 3 as 0 :- {3, 0}```.
So window/subarray size :-
```i - mp[3] + 1 == 3 - 0 + 1 == 4 ( [3, 4, 2, 3] )```**

T.C :- O(n)
S.C :- O(n) 

**Hope you found this helpful!**

