Here we traverse through the array and store the numbers with their index in unordered_map and while traversing we check if the element is present earlier in the map. If found, we find the distance between current index and previous index of the same element stored in the map.
We are using an unordered_map so space complexity will O(n) and we are traversing through the array once so time complexity will be O(n).
For finding the element the time taken on average is O(1) in unordered_map.

