# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The job is to find the closest pair of identical elements (A pair of identical having the minimum distance between them).

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We can create a hashmap/dictionary to store the following:
`card no. --> last index it was found at`

This way, when an element gets repeated, we know what index it was last found at, (since that is the instance of this element that would form a pair with minimum distance from the current element).

After calculating the distance, we can update the last index of that particular element to be the current index.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:$$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:$$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

